    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are looking for elite production out of the top of the order today, with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the card at a massive 81.88 efficiency score. His matchup against Bello is highly favorable, bolstered by a 16% park factor bump and a 14% platoon advantage that makes him the clear anchor of the lineup. Following closely, **Kyle Tucker** (73.75) remains a priority start against Jameson Taillon; his strong xwOBA and clean matchup profile ensure he maintains his status as an everyday cornerstone. While the middle of the order faces some grind, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.24) provides reliable stability against Williams, G, benefiting from an favorable 6% bump for his #3 spot in the order and a park that leans slightly toward his profile.\n\nStrategic differentiation in our bench decisions today centered on marginal gains in categories that move the needle. The most difficult cut was **Brady House**, whose 52.73 score sat on the precipice of starting consideration. While his high SP skill projection against Hudson, B suggested a strong floor, the optimizer opted for the combined efficiency of **Nasim Nunez** (60.13), whose switch-hitting versatility and positional security provided a higher overall contribution to our 5x5 totals. We are closely monitoring the risk profile for **Heliot Ramos**, whose score of 55.59 includes a slight \"Slow SP Delivery\" bonus\u2014a crucial detail for our strategy given that SB is our scarcest category. We are betting that Alcantara, S\u2019s rhythm will provide the opening **Heliot Ramos** needs to steal a bag. \n\nFinally, managers should keep a sharp eye on the **Liam Hicks** and **Drake Baldwin** tandem; both are serving as primary options today, but their scores are sensitive to the mid-tier matchups against Houser and Painter, respectively. **Marcell Ozuna** was restricted to the bench today with a low 42.53 score, largely due to the difficulty of his matchup against Woodruff, whose xERA of 2.90 makes him an elite arm that suppresses expectations for even our most potent hitters. We are playing for consistent daily efficiency to maximize our game caps without sacrificing our core advantage in speed and average.",
